cons:
If you're not perfect in French you're career will slow down latest after reaching Manager-Level - the number of non-French speakers at the top (Director/Partner) is very limited and depending on the business line;
Internal Trainings are often done by other colleagues which are not always have proper knowledge of the topic or on how to give trainings;
Performance Management process is not followed in reality and results are sometimes falsified on higher level without further explanation - contacting HR in this matter is not very helpful;
Due to the huge and still raising sales-pressure in all business lines, decisions and promotions are more and more made only for the personal benefit of the partnership without recognizing the work of all the ones that still support the base business;
The working conditions ("package") are getting worst from year to year: no separate office - no fixed workspace - physical documents and office material are not in easy reach - no car parking - more and more overtime which is not compensated;

pros:
Clear career-path defined;
Global Opportunities program for the transfer to other KPMG locations;
Events (for clients and sales-oriented employees) organized throughout the year;
Private Mobile phone use;
Lunch voucher;
External Trainings;
